Variable
A variable is a container that stores a value. These values can be changed during execution of program.

Rules fo declaring a variable name
-->We can choose a name while declaring a Java variable if following rules are followed :
1. Must not begin with a digit.
    (1rray --> not allowed)

2. Name is case sensitive
    (Honey and honey are different)

3. Should not be keyword.
        (Reserved words are called keywords, e.g. for, void, static etc.)
        (Void is acceptable)

4. White space not allowed.
    (int code with harry --> is not allowed,
     codeWithHarry is allowed)

5. Can contain alphabets, $ character, _ character and digits if other conditions are met.
       ( int age2 is allowed)
